02:02:56,078 --> 02:02:59,380
[SPEAKER_06]: I guess, over a certain amount, like doing the kitchens over?

1269
02:03:00,280 --> 02:03:05,043
[SPEAKER_06]: Is it our ordinance that we have to change that tells them that they have to do their water main?

1270
02:03:06,764 --> 02:03:10,466
[SPEAKER_10]: So that's something different than what we're discussing here.

1271
02:03:10,506 --> 02:03:11,887
[SPEAKER_10]: You're talking about... Right.

1272
02:03:11,907 --> 02:03:13,828
[SPEAKER_06]: You can talk about this offline if you want.

1273
02:03:13,868 --> 02:03:14,128
[SPEAKER_06]: Sure.

1274
02:03:15,228 --> 02:03:19,631
[SPEAKER_10]: You're talking about water service lines, like the direct line from the main to the house.

1275
02:03:20,451 --> 02:03:38,618
[SPEAKER_10]: And it's under the water sewer regulations that if you are doing a large renovation to your project over $30,000, then you need to identify the material if it is not, if it is lead or if our records indicate that it's lead or that it's indicated as unknown.

1276
02:03:39,358 --> 02:03:39,678
[SPEAKER_06]: Okay.

1277
02:03:39,718 --> 02:03:42,479
[SPEAKER_06]: So that's, that's, that's not with our ordinance.

1278
02:03:42,499 --> 02:03:43,080
[SPEAKER_06]: That's something that.

1279
02:03:43,140 --> 02:03:43,480
[SPEAKER_06]: Correct.

1280
02:03:43,580 --> 02:03:44,980
[SPEAKER_06]: That's the water and sewer regulations.

1281
02:03:45,040 --> 02:03:45,260
[SPEAKER_06]: All right.

1282
02:03:45,300 --> 02:03:47,321
[SPEAKER_06]: So I have other questions, but if Kim will talk offline.

1283
02:03:47,341 --> 02:03:47,561
[SPEAKER_06]: Sure.

1284
02:03:47,921 --> 02:03:49,122
[SPEAKER_06]: I think that, because I've,

1285
02:03:50,964 --> 02:03:52,727
