02:10:48,912 --> 02:10:49,493
[SPEAKER_02]: Councilor Malauulu.

1390
02:10:50,335 --> 02:10:50,615
[SPEAKER_12]: Thank you.

1391
02:10:50,635 --> 02:10:51,496
[SPEAKER_12]: Just a quick question.

1392
02:10:52,356 --> 02:10:58,019
[SPEAKER_12]: Just high level, what is the communication strategy or how are we letting these residents know when this is impacting them?

1393
02:10:58,439 --> 02:11:00,760
[SPEAKER_10]: So we have, sorry, are you good?

1394
02:11:01,360 --> 02:11:05,382
[SPEAKER_10]: So we've done kind of like an overhaul with the communications basis.

1395
02:11:05,462 --> 02:11:09,324
[SPEAKER_10]: We've wrapped in the administration's communications director.

1396
02:11:09,724 --> 02:11:12,105
[SPEAKER_10]: We do reverse 911 calls.

1397
02:11:12,686 --> 02:11:16,848
[SPEAKER_10]: We message this out usually as soon as the contractor

1398
02:11:17,708 --> 02:11:38,446
[SPEAKER_10]: schedules the work, we post, we do door-to-door flyers as well, and then we call, and then we put barrels with a big, like no parking signs, and it usually has more information on that, where it's like water work, you know, for the next couple weeks.

1399
02:11:38,986 --> 02:11:43,750
[SPEAKER_10]: And usually when we first fly a flyer, we'll get an influx of calls and, you know,

1400
02:11:44,691 --> 02:11:50,892
[SPEAKER_10]: We'll discuss like how it's going to be phased to, you know, residents that are curious about it.

1401
02:11:51,272 --> 02:11:57,574
[SPEAKER_10]: And usually the big concerns are like where's parking, when's it going to do, you know, what are the hours.

1402
02:11:58,734 --> 02:12:05,315
[SPEAKER_10]: And for the most part, the water main work is pretty fast moving so it's not usually lingering in front of a, you know, one resident.

1403
02:12:07,316 --> 02:12:07,916
[SPEAKER_10]: That's about it.

1404
02:12:08,216 --> 02:12:08,376
[SPEAKER_10]: Yeah.

1405
02:12:10,056 --> 02:12:10,256
[SPEAKER_02]: All right.

1406
02:12:10,336 --> 02:12:10,576
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

1407
