[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you, Owen.

1427
02:12:48,156 --> 02:12:48,516
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

1428
02:12:48,976 --> 02:12:54,857
[SPEAKER_02]: 26114 submitted by Mayor Brianna Longo-Kern, Medford Public Schools Special Purpose Override Stabilization Fund Appropriation.

1429
02:12:55,878 --> 02:13:00,739
[SPEAKER_02]: This stabilization fund was established in the previous fiscal year.

1430
02:13:01,719 --> 02:13:08,721
[SPEAKER_02]: As folks know, the November 2024 overrides occurred in the middle of a fiscal year.

1431
02:13:09,981 --> 02:13:13,782
[SPEAKER_02]: And those funds were directed to the Medford Public Schools

1432
02:13:15,762 --> 02:13:16,603
[SPEAKER_02]: for their programming.

1433
02:13:17,203 --> 02:13:31,951
[SPEAKER_02]: At the end of fiscal 25, there was a sum that was unexpended because it was done halfway through the fiscal year, so those funds were retained in a special purpose stabilization fund for future use by Medford Public Schools.

1434
02:13:33,012 --> 02:13:39,015
[SPEAKER_02]: Questions 7 and 8 did both go to fund our schools in fiscal year 2025 and 2026 and are fully utilized in fiscal 27.

1435
02:13:43,317 --> 02:14:11,717
[SPEAKER_02]: One of the main things that they are funding is the contract with the Medford Teachers Association and its members which resulted in significant wage and benefit increases as well as the finally the solution to addressing the high school schedule which allows every student at Medford High School to take arts, music, vocational courses in addition to their academic core courses which has been long awaited.

1436
02:14:13,078 --> 02:14:14,699
[SPEAKER_02]: That's a very, very short overview.

1437
02:14:14,739 --> 02:14:18,081
[SPEAKER_02]: The specific paper from the mayor is from June 4th, 2026.

1438
02:14:19,662 --> 02:14:36,193
[SPEAKER_02]: Dear President Beers and city councilors, I respectfully request and recommend your honorable body approves an appropriation of $1,085,549.00 from the Medford Public Schools Special Purpose Override Stabilization Fund as per the city council's June 24th, 2025 vote in accordance with the enclosed recommendation.

1439
02:14:36,973 --> 02:14:39,654
[SPEAKER_02]: to establish and transfer funds to the Stabilization Fund.

1440
02:14:39,714 --> 02:14:43,455
[SPEAKER_02]: The Medford Public Schools Special Purpose Override Stabilization Fund currently has a balance of $2,185,000.

1441
02:14:45,855 --> 02:14:49,456
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you for your kind attention to this matter, respectfully submitted Brianna Lungelkern, Mayor.

1442
02:14:49,936 --> 02:15:01,379
[SPEAKER_02]: So in that enclosure which established the fund, we also received a presentation last June outlining how the funds would be expended over a three fiscal year period with about a million dollars this year, around 500 or 600,000 next year.

1443
02:15:01,399 --> 02:15:02,259
[SPEAKER_02]: You'll correct me.

1444
02:15:05,740 --> 02:15:12,844
[SPEAKER_02]: and then the remainder, which is a little around, I think around 400,000 in the year after that.

1445
02:15:13,285 --> 02:15:17,627
[SPEAKER_02]: So kind of winding down that funds while supporting the Medford Public Schools.

1446
02:15:17,727 --> 02:15:24,731
[SPEAKER_02]: And we have the Medford Public Schools Director of Finance, Noel Vela is here, so I will turn it over to him to share anything else.

1447
02:15:25,732 --> 02:15:30,615
[SPEAKER_00]: Yeah, no, as you just said, you know, our goal is to continue to support our teachers, continue to support,

1448
02:15:31,923 --> 02:15:34,905
[SPEAKER_00]: higher education and greater education here at Medford Public Schools.

1449
02:15:36,566 --> 02:15:53,114
[SPEAKER_00]: So this $1,085,549 will go into approximately 29 accounts and also into our stipends and coaches accounts because also as part of the CBA, we also increases our stipends to our coaches.

1450
02:15:53,654 --> 02:16:03,202
[SPEAKER_00]: who support our athletic students, and we also increased our stipends for after school activities and providing more extracurricular activities after school.

1451
02:16:03,262 --> 02:16:08,106
[SPEAKER_00]: And we wanted these stipends to be competitive with other communities around our area.

1452
02:16:08,146 --> 02:16:18,795
[SPEAKER_00]: So the stabilization fund continues to go into those areas, continues to lift up our budget, and more importantly, have a positive impact on our students.

1453
02:16:20,187 --> 02:16:20,507
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

