1529
02:21:16,660 --> 02:21:25,684
[SPEAKER_02]: If there's any additional comments in addition to all the budget meetings that we've had that you'd like to share right now or any, I know there was some changes in the book.

1530
02:21:25,864 --> 02:21:29,906
[SPEAKER_02]: If you want to go over those, let us know and then we'll take it from there.

1531
02:21:33,964 --> 02:21:34,244
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you.

1532
02:21:34,424 --> 02:21:35,184
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you, President Behrs.

1533
02:21:35,965 --> 02:21:36,785
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you for that.

1534
02:21:37,065 --> 02:21:44,907
[SPEAKER_01]: I appreciate all of that, the high-level overview, the opportunity to speak before you all with regard to this FY27 proposed budget.

1535
02:21:44,947 --> 02:21:52,270
[SPEAKER_01]: I appreciate all the time that the councilors have put into hearing the budget proposals from department heads, and I know it's been a

1536
02:21:53,556 --> 02:22:01,789
[SPEAKER_01]: lengthy process for all of you and for all of us, candidly, by just some high-level background items.

1537
02:22:03,051 --> 02:22:06,377
[SPEAKER_01]: In February, we sent out budget sheets which were due back in March.

1538
02:22:06,497 --> 02:22:07,999
[SPEAKER_01]: In April, we learned that there was a

1539
02:22:09,411 --> 02:22:18,264
[SPEAKER_01]: A substantive and large school budget gap through April and May and somewhat into June, we were closing the gap between the revenue and proposed expenditures.

1540
02:22:18,304 --> 02:22:23,752
[SPEAKER_01]: I know the council knows all of this, but in case this is the first time a member of the public is tuning into these discussions.

1541
02:22:24,312 --> 02:22:35,482
[SPEAKER_01]: I want to thank all the department heads who contributed to this process and also worked collaboratively with us, myself, the mayor, the finance team, to adjust budgets as needed.

1542
02:22:36,163 --> 02:22:49,335
[SPEAKER_01]: As the council knows, the mayor sent the council an email following her presentation on June 2nd, identifying a proposal that was the result of the council's 15-page memo, as well as feedback from the council and the councilors, which we appreciate.

1543
02:22:49,915 --> 02:23:03,665
[SPEAKER_01]: The mayor sent the council over a half a dozen emails addressing the inquiries and requests by the council as a part of their FY27 priorities, as well as feedback from, which included feedback from department heads.

1544
02:23:06,637 --> 02:23:29,325
[SPEAKER_01]: It also indicated that through cuts we would be providing $1.25 million additionally to the schools, which wasn't originally part of the allocation that was identified for the school department when it was communicated in the, in February as per the budget ordinance by our finance director and auditor, Bob Dickinson, who is here this evening.

1545
02:23:31,444 --> 02:23:44,998
[SPEAKER_01]: The mayor also shared that she was prepared to add over $112,000 to the FY27 proposed budget with additional funding to recreation, arts, library, legislative and law budgets conditioned upon a package budget deal.

1546
02:23:45,398 --> 02:23:52,185
[SPEAKER_01]: The mayor was also happy to share the $50,000 grant from Tufts to the Medford Family Network and a Cummings grant for $100,000.

1547
02:23:53,806 --> 02:24:11,374
[SPEAKER_01]: and indicated in that communication, I know you all know this, so please bear with me as I go through, but $157,000 roughly would be a bridge to the Medford Family Network through free cash based on discussions with members of the council.

1548
02:24:12,414 --> 02:24:18,837
[SPEAKER_01]: And as proposed, so that would be for the June 23rd meeting before the council.

1549
02:24:20,800 --> 02:24:33,063
[SPEAKER_01]: As you all know, the mayor is happy to discuss with any councilor these details and we appreciate the communications back from a couple of councilors who had a chance to reply to that communication by the mayor.

1550
02:24:34,264 --> 02:24:42,626
[SPEAKER_01]: President Bares, you had asked that we identify changes between the department budget submitted at the hearings and at the final budget that are in the final budget book.

1551
02:24:42,686 --> 02:24:44,106
[SPEAKER_01]: So we did our best to outline those.

1552
02:24:44,166 --> 02:24:47,908
[SPEAKER_01]: I have some copies of that information here.

1553
02:24:47,968 --> 02:24:49,388
[SPEAKER_01]: If it's all right, I'll pass that out.

1554
02:24:51,112 --> 02:24:51,377
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you.

1555
02:25:32,772 --> 02:25:36,595
[SPEAKER_01]: As you will see on the list before you, there was a change in the building department.

1556
02:25:37,236 --> 02:25:45,763
[SPEAKER_01]: I've outlined the specific line in which there was a change, the original amount that came before the council, the final amount, and whether it was an increase or decrease.

1557
02:25:46,584 --> 02:25:52,569
[SPEAKER_01]: So I'll just go through the department and the amount and what it was essentially for.

1558
02:25:53,329 --> 02:26:09,847
[SPEAKER_01]: To be brief, for the building department, the increase was about 13, well, it was $13,290, and it was to consolidate citizen-serve licenses across various departments, which I believe was shared with the council on a few different occasions.

1559
02:26:10,027 --> 02:26:12,370
[SPEAKER_01]: One namely was the city clerk's office, another one

1560
02:26:13,030 --> 02:26:18,695
[SPEAKER_01]: And they'll come up throughout this list so I will kind of see that redundant.

1561
02:26:18,835 --> 02:26:21,077
[SPEAKER_01]: And that's a perfect segue to the next line.

1562
02:26:21,497 --> 02:26:32,786
[SPEAKER_01]: The clerk's budget was reduced by eighteen hundred dollars because the citizens served licenses that were proposed in that budget or the license if I'm not mistaken was moved to the building department.

1563
02:26:34,040 --> 02:26:38,182
[SPEAKER_01]: For the engineering division, there was an adjustment of a decrease of $10,500.

1564
02:26:39,682 --> 02:26:43,403
[SPEAKER_01]: Again, this was a citizen served consolidation into the building department.

1565
02:26:44,364 --> 02:26:47,305
[SPEAKER_01]: And I'm going to jump down for a moment to

1566
02:26:49,833 --> 02:27:00,342
[SPEAKER_01]: the second Health and Human Services line for the last adjustment pertaining to CitizenServe, which was a decrease in that department of $4,500.

1567
02:27:00,422 --> 02:27:12,132
[SPEAKER_01]: I also want to note that it didn't end up being apples for apples because we communicated with the vendor who was proposing to go from $1,500 per license to $1,800 per license in FY27 and asked for a reduction in that.

1568
02:27:17,977 --> 02:27:23,379
[SPEAKER_01]: And they did agree to bridging half of that increase over two fiscal years.

1569
02:27:23,459 --> 02:27:31,501
[SPEAKER_01]: So the license cost per license is actually now going to be for fiscal 27, $1,650 per license.

1570
02:27:31,861 --> 02:27:33,242
[SPEAKER_01]: So happy about that.

1571
02:27:34,522 --> 02:27:36,723
[SPEAKER_01]: It's a temporary measure, but at least it is some cost savings.

1572
02:27:39,526 --> 02:27:54,010
[SPEAKER_01]: On the next item, I was largely focused on identifying things that were about $1,000, but I didn't want to exclude something in the executive budget because I wanted to make sure I was inordinarily transparent about that.

1573
02:27:54,110 --> 02:27:59,252
[SPEAKER_01]: I had missed a longevity item for that office, for the executive office, for the office that I work in.

1574
02:27:59,972 --> 02:28:02,833
[SPEAKER_01]: It wasn't for me, but it was for another staff member, so I added that.

1575
02:28:02,873 --> 02:28:03,073
[SPEAKER_01]: That was $950.

1576
02:28:05,234 --> 02:28:17,526
[SPEAKER_01]: In finance, there was a $3,801.98 change because it was a correction on the personnel line that was identified in the budget hearing by a member of the council at the time.

1577
02:28:18,567 --> 02:28:22,632
[SPEAKER_01]: Health and human services, under the permanent employees line, there was a reduction of $76,411.96.

1578
02:28:26,415 --> 02:28:34,719
[SPEAKER_01]: And there was a grant funded employee who was inadvertently listed basically in the grant section of the budget and also in the general fund section of the budget.

1579
02:28:36,300 --> 02:28:40,142
[SPEAKER_01]: We already went over the next line, which was the citizen served for the $4,500 for health and human services.

1580
02:28:42,879 --> 02:28:52,466
[SPEAKER_01]: For legislative, through communications with you, Councilor Behrs, we added $10,000 to account for the citizen-serve costs that you had mentioned at the budget hearing for legislative.

1581
02:28:53,267 --> 02:28:56,089
[SPEAKER_01]: For the library, there was a reduction of $100,609.35.

1582
02:28:58,011 --> 02:29:04,576
[SPEAKER_01]: As presented by the library director, there was an inadvertent duplication in salaries during that budget hearing that was stated.

1583
02:29:05,436 --> 02:29:15,802
[SPEAKER_01]: And then finally, with two minor notes after this, for the Treasury and Collections Department, there was an increase in $7,000 to move SoftRite to the cloud.

1584
02:29:16,182 --> 02:29:20,084
[SPEAKER_01]: SoftRite is the vendor that the city uses to input collections.

1585
02:29:21,105 --> 02:29:23,226
[SPEAKER_01]: The reality is if we were, you know,

1586
02:29:27,010 --> 02:29:31,251
[SPEAKER_01]: If it was easy to move to a new financial package software, we wouldn't have to do this.

1587
02:29:31,431 --> 02:29:35,892
[SPEAKER_01]: But it's going to take several years, as we all know, to move to a new financial software.

1588
02:29:35,912 --> 02:29:43,994
[SPEAKER_01]: And the most efficient way to go through that process, where our current server is end of life for SoftRite, would be to move to the cloud.

1589
02:29:44,394 --> 02:29:46,435
[SPEAKER_01]: And so that will come with a $7,000 cost.

1590
02:29:46,475 --> 02:29:49,995
[SPEAKER_01]: I got those numbers right around when this budget package was being finalized.

1591
02:29:50,055 --> 02:29:53,356
[SPEAKER_01]: So, you know, it seemed prudent to put it in.

1592
02:29:53,776 --> 02:29:56,437
[SPEAKER_01]: We will also probably be before the council for a

1593
02:29:57,537 --> 02:30:13,966
[SPEAKER_01]: appropriation for the admin server, the other financial software that the city uses because that server is also end of life and we're doing our due diligence to address issues that could come up later down the road in these areas.

1594
02:30:14,887 --> 02:30:17,909
[SPEAKER_01]: And then there was minor changes to the elections and facilities departments.

1595
02:30:17,969 --> 02:30:23,892
[SPEAKER_01]: Both of those were under $1,000 and in one case it was mainly moving between a couple of lines.

1596
02:30:25,105 --> 02:30:27,066
[SPEAKER_01]: Happy to answer any questions on that.

1597
02:30:28,747 --> 02:30:46,197
[SPEAKER_01]: And one other thing I'll point out, if it's easiest for me to just go through all the comments, is we replaced pages 59 and 60 in your budget books, given an error that was flagged on Friday afternoon, but we couldn't correct before delivering the books to the council by Friday at noon.

1598
02:30:46,957 --> 02:30:56,020
[SPEAKER_01]: And then finally, the FY27 proposed water and sewer budget, that's in the transmittal letter before you all, contains a scrivener's error.

1599
02:30:56,060 --> 02:30:59,981
[SPEAKER_01]: The line that contains the water and sewer budget simply has an addition error.

1600
02:31:00,622 --> 02:31:06,864
[SPEAKER_01]: It states that the line for the overall water and sewer budget, not including bonds and interest, is $27,799,042.18, when it should in fact be $27,700,000

1601
02:31:18,728 --> 02:31:25,733
[SPEAKER_01]: $742,000.18.

1602
02:31:21,150 --> 02:31:25,733
[SPEAKER_01]: All the other numbers are correct, including the water and sewer total.

1603
02:31:26,093 --> 02:31:26,413
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you.

1604
02:31:28,675 --> 02:31:30,176
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you, Madam Chief of Staff.

1605
02:31:31,957 --> 02:31:40,043
[SPEAKER_02]: I just had, I think even on the corrected pages 59 and 60, I think the school budget is still, it says fiscal 27 is $85,490,000.

1606
02:31:40,243 --> 02:31:41,824
[SPEAKER_02]: And I think you guys are proposing $89.1.

1607
02:31:41,864 --> 02:31:43,665
[SPEAKER_02]: So I just wanted to double check on that.

1608
02:31:47,722 --> 02:31:48,623
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you for flagging that.

1609
02:31:48,643 --> 02:31:49,163
[SPEAKER_01]: We'll review.

1610
02:31:49,544 --> 02:31:49,824
[SPEAKER_02]: Okay.

1611
02:31:50,344 --> 02:31:50,605
[SPEAKER_02]: Great.

1612
02:31:52,947 --> 02:31:54,628
[SPEAKER_02]: You know, I don't know if we'll move ahead tonight.

1613
02:31:55,949 --> 02:31:57,971
[SPEAKER_02]: If not, a revised version would be great.

1614
02:31:58,071 --> 02:32:08,840
[SPEAKER_02]: And just like a general FYI, procedurally, we are, next week as you are aware is riddled with holidays.

1615
02:32:10,193 --> 02:32:14,037
[SPEAKER_02]: We are trying to set a deadline of Tuesday afternoon for papers.

1616
02:32:15,538 --> 02:32:16,579
[SPEAKER_02]: I know that's going to be tough.

1617
02:32:17,439 --> 02:32:19,001
[SPEAKER_02]: I'm happy to discuss it further with you.

1618
02:32:19,561 --> 02:32:25,145
[SPEAKER_02]: But for the June 23rd meeting where we just have some deadline, it's tough with the Wednesday and the Friday.

1619
02:32:25,386 --> 02:32:25,586
[SPEAKER_02]: So.

1620
02:32:26,106 --> 02:32:26,467
[SPEAKER_01]: Understood.

1621
02:32:26,867 --> 02:32:35,234
[SPEAKER_02]: And with the short staffing continuing in the clerk's office and the acting clerk is, you know, planning on using PTO as this is right on so.

1622
02:32:35,974 --> 02:32:41,597
[SPEAKER_02]: We just really, anything we could have by Tuesday, even earlier than that would be really helpful.

1623
02:32:42,438 --> 02:32:43,198
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you, President Perez.

1624
02:32:43,218 --> 02:32:44,819
[SPEAKER_01]: I appreciate the heads up and we'll do everything we can.

1625
02:32:44,899 --> 02:32:45,280
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

1626
02:32:45,400 --> 02:32:48,041
[SPEAKER_02]: I'll go to Vice President Lazaro and then Councilor Scarpelli.

1627
02:32:49,182 --> 02:32:50,282
[SPEAKER_03]: No, I turned it off.

1628
02:32:50,703 --> 02:32:51,303
[SPEAKER_02]: Oh, okay.

1629
02:32:51,943 --> 02:32:53,324
[SPEAKER_02]: Councilor Scarpelli.

1630
02:32:53,364 --> 02:32:54,405
[SPEAKER_06]: Thank you, Mr. President.

1631
02:32:54,425 --> 02:33:01,029
[SPEAKER_06]: So, first, I want to first apologize for last week.

1632
02:33:01,129 --> 02:33:02,309
[SPEAKER_06]: I was on the meeting.

1633
02:33:02,369 --> 02:33:03,230
[SPEAKER_06]: I can hear everything.

1634
02:33:04,498 --> 02:33:12,521
[SPEAKER_06]: For some reason, I couldn't send a message back, and that's why I was texting Council President.

1635
02:33:13,241 --> 02:33:22,143
[SPEAKER_06]: And I appreciate Clerk Alessio with the knowledge of not voting without being present.

1636
02:33:22,183 --> 02:33:23,004
[SPEAKER_06]: So I appreciate that.

1637
02:33:23,024 --> 02:33:25,745
[SPEAKER_06]: But I did hear some things last week.

1638
02:33:25,765 --> 02:33:32,347
[SPEAKER_06]: I would not be true to myself if I didn't follow through what we talked about.

1639
02:33:34,320 --> 02:33:46,292
[SPEAKER_06]: We have asked the city for legal documentation through FOIA to help us understand our true financial picture and our true financial gaps that are occurring in this community.

1640
02:33:48,154 --> 02:33:55,678
[SPEAKER_06]: in understanding what the processes are and if it's something that's hurting us before we move forward with this budget vote.

1641
02:33:56,859 --> 02:34:11,587
[SPEAKER_06]: Last week, I heard the mayor come up and she explained again, which she was right, a thousand percent correct, that she presented us with a report that showed where we are in our legal line compared to neighboring communities.

1642
02:34:11,647 --> 02:34:12,168
[SPEAKER_06]: And she's right.

1643
02:34:13,008 --> 02:34:16,289
[SPEAKER_06]: But this is what I've been saying for many, many years now.

1644
02:34:16,969 --> 02:34:18,829
[SPEAKER_06]: That's not what we're asking for.

1645
02:34:18,929 --> 02:34:25,051
[SPEAKER_06]: What we're asking for, that's why the foyer is so detailed and asking for specific numbers.

1646
02:34:25,991 --> 02:34:33,232
[SPEAKER_06]: And the numbers that the mayor quoted were the numbers for our legal line.

1647
02:34:33,693 --> 02:34:35,213
[SPEAKER_06]: But it's not what we're spending.

1648
02:34:36,084 --> 02:34:46,369
[SPEAKER_06]: on legal issues throughout our community especially with what we're seeing for settlements and fighting lawsuits for our city employees and on and on.

1649
02:34:47,450 --> 02:34:57,255
[SPEAKER_06]: We asked for that information and it's funny because I know that the the administration said just a lot of work and you need to be it's difficult for us to do everything at once okay

1650
02:34:58,708 --> 02:35:14,236
[SPEAKER_06]: When the firefighters union came up, they expressed that this year alone they spent fighting the city's, the mayor's issues with the union members, that they spent $158,000, if I'm not correct, and they had them in line.

1651
02:35:14,336 --> 02:35:17,498
[SPEAKER_06]: They sent us an email breaking down, it's very simple.

1652
02:35:18,138 --> 02:35:22,279
[SPEAKER_06]: I mean, if we got just this, it might have appeased me saying, OK, this makes sense.

1653
02:35:22,879 --> 02:35:27,780
[SPEAKER_06]: But they sent every single legal line from what they've had since 2022.

1654
02:35:28,000 --> 02:35:31,560
[SPEAKER_06]: And it broke it down that they spent over $300,000.

1655
02:35:31,920 --> 02:35:40,202
[SPEAKER_06]: Now, that's with them fighting it, but then winning most of those cases.

1656
02:35:42,242 --> 02:35:47,183
[SPEAKER_06]: So this is the reason why I cannot move forward with

1657
02:35:48,402 --> 02:35:51,224
[SPEAKER_06]: approving or voting for this budget favorably tonight.

1658
02:35:52,144 --> 02:36:09,033
[SPEAKER_06]: I'm going to actually ask to table this, Mr. President, until our next meeting, which is the last Tuesday of the month of June, which hopefully gives us enough time to get that information that we're needing so we can make a strong decision whether

1659
02:36:10,211 --> 02:36:24,720
[SPEAKER_06]: There are concerns financially and then the other piece I would recommend the city administration prepare a 12-1 budget if that doesn't happen and that would be general law 44 section 22 chapter 44 section 22 that still has to

1660
02:36:29,634 --> 02:36:36,280
[SPEAKER_06]: budget our city, but on a month-to-month basis until we get the information that we need.

1661
02:36:37,221 --> 02:36:44,908
[SPEAKER_06]: And I find it funny that the mayor's response to the request that we asked for, there's stipulation that said what?

1662
02:36:45,508 --> 02:36:49,572
[SPEAKER_06]: As long as you don't cut the legal lines.

1663
02:36:53,856 --> 02:36:54,937
[SPEAKER_06]: That speaks volumes to me.

1664
02:36:56,577 --> 02:37:13,262
[SPEAKER_06]: So I would move, Mr. President, to table this to our next scheduled city council meeting and prepare our administration to, if not given the information that we need, to protect our community.

1665
02:37:13,502 --> 02:37:21,384
[SPEAKER_06]: And what we are charged to do is protect the fiscal responsibilities of this community without understanding what we're spending and

1666
02:37:22,032 --> 02:37:40,339
[SPEAKER_06]: We were pretty detailed on that FOIA, that understanding what the premiums are going to be, who's paying these lawsuits out, how much these lawsuits are for, how much we're paying attorneys, what attorneys other than KP Law, because there's multiple, and then moving forward with non-disclosure.

1667
02:37:40,379 --> 02:37:42,180
[SPEAKER_06]: That was disingenuine as well.

1668
02:37:42,820 --> 02:37:56,370
[SPEAKER_06]: with the first response saying that there has never been a non-disclosure process in the process of legalities, which is totally false because that was sent to me with a few different settlements.

1669
02:37:56,410 --> 02:37:58,612
[SPEAKER_06]: So there's a lot of information.

1670
02:37:58,852 --> 02:38:00,914
[SPEAKER_06]: I know it's a lot, but this is something new.

1671
02:38:01,594 --> 02:38:04,877
[SPEAKER_06]: Go back four years, I've asked the same exact question for four years.

1672
02:38:06,251 --> 02:38:13,317
[SPEAKER_06]: It's just, I appreciate that my counselors are now seeing that and they understand the process.

1673
02:38:13,337 --> 02:38:16,479
[SPEAKER_06]: So I appreciate that, Mr. President, and I move to table.

1674
02:38:17,480 --> 02:38:26,567
[SPEAKER_02]: If I may request, Councilor Scarpelli, that you withdraw the motion since it is undebatable, just in case any other counselors have anything they want to say, and then I might have a question.

1675
02:38:26,607 --> 02:38:28,209
[SPEAKER_06]: Okay, I would respect that.

1676
02:38:28,249 --> 02:38:29,710
[SPEAKER_06]: I would take that off for now.

1677
02:38:29,890 --> 02:38:30,170
[SPEAKER_02]: Great.

1678
02:38:30,611 --> 02:38:32,232
[SPEAKER_02]: Is there anything else from any other counselors?

1679
02:38:35,597 --> 02:38:36,418
[SPEAKER_02]: Councilor Callahan.

1680
02:38:38,720 --> 02:38:55,413
[SPEAKER_14]: Yeah I was I was going to say that as I was looking at this final budget I really did appreciate the many places where the administration did do what we requested with the librarians the you know

1681
02:38:55,883 --> 02:39:07,988
[SPEAKER_14]: increasing just a little bit more to pay for the lowest paid librarians, the part-time hourly librarians, also funding the charter mandated position that supports the city council.

1682
02:39:09,308 --> 02:39:11,389
[SPEAKER_14]: However, as I looked at this budget,

1683
02:39:14,490 --> 02:39:22,117
[SPEAKER_14]: The law department budget is the one that I have difficulty with.

1684
02:39:22,137 --> 02:39:25,180
[SPEAKER_14]: And we requested information.

1685
02:39:25,200 --> 02:39:26,561
[SPEAKER_14]: We couldn't get that information.

1686
02:39:26,601 --> 02:39:28,002
[SPEAKER_14]: We put in a FOIA request.

1687
02:39:28,242 --> 02:39:31,025
[SPEAKER_14]: I don't know exactly what day that FOIA request is.

1688
02:39:33,262 --> 02:39:34,603
[SPEAKER_14]: in terms of I think it's only.

1689
02:39:34,623 --> 02:39:36,203
[SPEAKER_02]: There was a 30-day extension.

1690
02:39:36,283 --> 02:39:37,083
[SPEAKER_02]: I'm not 100% sure.

1691
02:39:37,104 --> 02:39:38,504
[SPEAKER_14]: 30-day extension.

1692
02:39:38,524 --> 02:39:39,544
[SPEAKER_14]: So I don't know.

1693
02:39:39,564 --> 02:39:46,867
[SPEAKER_14]: I think we've said before that like this would be important information for us to understand before approving the budget, and yet we don't have that information.

1694
02:39:47,247 --> 02:39:50,788
[SPEAKER_14]: So it feels quite disappointing.

1695
02:39:53,289 --> 02:39:53,649
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

1696
02:39:53,709 --> 02:39:55,910
[SPEAKER_02]: Any further comments from members of the council?

1697
02:40:05,208 --> 02:40:08,210
[SPEAKER_20]: I was just going to say I think it makes sense to table this.

1698
02:40:10,111 --> 02:40:12,653
[SPEAKER_20]: I know we're not supposed to debate that.

1699
02:40:14,574 --> 02:40:17,096
[SPEAKER_20]: But that's my personal preference.

1700
02:40:20,858 --> 02:40:35,830
[SPEAKER_20]: There are some new changes, I know they're mostly, the explanations make sense, but I think it makes sense for councillors to sit with us a little bit longer and make sure that we do have everything we want in here.

1701
02:40:36,831 --> 02:40:46,019
[SPEAKER_20]: I also, as Councillor Scarpelli alluded to, the offer is to add a number of things that we want with the

1702
02:40:46,967 --> 02:40:54,910
[SPEAKER_20]: understanding that we won't cut the legal service line item, call that a deal.

1703
02:40:56,011 --> 02:41:16,539
[SPEAKER_20]: But I think in order to understand if this is the best deal for our residents, for our city services, and for our taxpayer money, it makes sense to get as much information as we can from the administration with respect to what we're looking for on the FOIA and with the legal line items that

1704
02:41:17,427 --> 02:41:27,199
[SPEAKER_20]: Not only in the law department budget, but also the ones that are being used across departments as well Thank You counselor saying

1705
02:41:28,780 --> 02:41:31,621
[SPEAKER_02]: Seeing no further questions from members of the council, I do have a few.

1706
02:41:31,641 --> 02:41:54,125
[SPEAKER_02]: I think it would be helpful, I don't know if you want to do it tonight or if you want to put it in writing and attach it to the agenda to kind of go through publicly with the public the proposal that the mayor is offering, essentially that certain things, 5,000 for the Arts Council, the Arts Liaison, a raise for the librarians, the council city messenger and council assistant.

1707
02:41:56,685 --> 02:41:59,247
[SPEAKER_02]: And I'm not sure if the MFN is in this or not.

1708
02:41:59,307 --> 02:42:03,751
[SPEAKER_02]: I couldn't quite tell from the email.

1709
02:42:04,171 --> 02:42:14,119
[SPEAKER_02]: But kind of explaining what is, which of these things are contingent on us not making cuts to the budget?

1710
02:42:14,199 --> 02:42:17,462
[SPEAKER_02]: You know, what are the things that aren't going to be funded?

1711
02:42:18,967 --> 02:42:23,991
[SPEAKER_02]: if the council continues to hold through its concerns about the legal expenses.

1712
02:42:24,071 --> 02:42:29,955
[SPEAKER_02]: And I think the other thing is back to what the other councilors requested, which is, you know, the questions are still there.

1713
02:42:30,075 --> 02:42:36,480
[SPEAKER_02]: I mean, some of them, obviously, there's a lot in the initial request from early this year and the public records request that we made.

1714
02:42:37,020 --> 02:42:44,282
[SPEAKER_02]: There were also some pretty specific requests in the budget meetings, like a breakdown of the professional services and the fire.

1715
02:42:44,302 --> 02:42:53,605
[SPEAKER_02]: You know, Chief Evans kind of verbally described to us a breakdown of that line item, but he did not.

1716
02:42:55,346 --> 02:42:57,706
[SPEAKER_02]: We asked for a written copy of that.

1717
02:42:59,887 --> 02:43:02,668
[SPEAKER_02]: So that is a...

1718
02:43:04,615 --> 02:43:18,621
[SPEAKER_02]: I think those are a few of the things that I'm hearing counselors outline, but for me very specifically, you know, I have a difficult time that, I have a hard time with, we will fund these things.

1719
02:43:18,961 --> 02:43:20,562
[SPEAKER_02]: We know the money's there to fund these things.

1720
02:43:20,622 --> 02:43:22,063
[SPEAKER_02]: We agree that these things are important.

1721
02:43:22,183 --> 02:43:31,347
[SPEAKER_02]: We just had, you know, two hours tonight with the Arts Council talking about the Arts Council needing more money, wanting to bring back the liaison.

1722
02:43:31,927 --> 02:43:34,288
[SPEAKER_02]: And it's like, we will only fund those things if you don't,

1723
02:43:36,062 --> 02:43:42,668
[SPEAKER_02]: you know, if you back down on your oversight, you know, specifically around the legal budget.

1724
02:43:42,688 --> 02:43:43,930
[SPEAKER_02]: So I have a hard time with that.

1725
02:43:44,410 --> 02:43:50,416
[SPEAKER_02]: I think that's a discussion that shouldn't be had kind of as indicated in the mayor's email.

1726
02:43:51,708 --> 02:43:53,249
[SPEAKER_02]: in private one-on-one conversations.

1727
02:43:53,269 --> 02:43:57,270
[SPEAKER_02]: I think that's a conversation that we should have here on the floor of the chamber.

1728
02:43:57,531 --> 02:44:02,193
[SPEAKER_02]: I think the administration should present that clearly to us, like here.

1729
02:44:02,213 --> 02:44:06,174
[SPEAKER_02]: Not necessarily just paragraphs in an email, but here's what the budget will look like.

1730
02:44:08,658 --> 02:44:11,700
[SPEAKER_02]: here are the amendments that we're proposing to the budget to fund these priorities.

1731
02:44:13,081 --> 02:44:26,632
[SPEAKER_02]: And also be clear that, you know, if the Arts Council doesn't get more funding this next year or there's no liaison or there's no council assistant or the rec department doesn't get its money or we decide not to give librarians

1732
02:44:27,460 --> 02:44:35,947
[SPEAKER_02]: a $4 an hour raise instead of a $2 an hour raise, that that's because the mayor said that's only happening if you guys don't cut KP law.

1733
02:44:36,288 --> 02:44:38,770
[SPEAKER_02]: So I think that should be a discussion that's had in public.

1734
02:44:39,390 --> 02:44:42,393
[SPEAKER_02]: I don't think that's a discussion that should be had behind closed doors.

1735
02:44:42,413 --> 02:44:45,035
[SPEAKER_02]: I don't think it's a discussion I'm comfortable having behind closed doors.

1736
02:44:45,135 --> 02:44:51,200
[SPEAKER_02]: So I would really like to see that presented as a paper when we take this back up.

1737
02:44:52,800 --> 02:44:58,263
[SPEAKER_02]: And it's all written out here largely, although I'd like to kind of see it in budget format versus kind of this written paragraph format.

1738
02:44:58,863 --> 02:45:09,009
[SPEAKER_02]: But I'd like to see that be something that the administration presents as essentially saying this is what's required to fund these things.

1739
02:45:09,149 --> 02:45:10,370
[SPEAKER_02]: So that's my personal preference.

1740
02:45:10,390 --> 02:45:12,091
[SPEAKER_02]: I don't know if other counselors have comments on that.

1741
02:45:12,691 --> 02:45:15,452
[SPEAKER_02]: It does look like at least Counselor Callahan has more to say.

1742
02:45:15,532 --> 02:45:19,415
[SPEAKER_02]: So I'll go to her and then I'll let you guys kind

1743
02:45:20,498 --> 02:45:24,819
[SPEAKER_02]: respond and we can engage in a dialogue, and then it sounds like Councilor Scarpelli wants to motion to table.

1744
02:45:24,900 --> 02:45:30,842
[SPEAKER_02]: So I will go to Councilor Callahan, then Councilor Mullane, then Councilor Sang, and then you guys.

1745
02:45:32,562 --> 02:45:37,164
[SPEAKER_14]: I simply wanted to mention that I did read this email from the mayor.

1746
02:45:37,184 --> 02:45:46,647
[SPEAKER_14]: I completely missed the half sentence that said that it was contingent upon us not cutting the legal budget.

1747
02:45:46,687 --> 02:45:48,888
[SPEAKER_14]: So I totally missed that part of it.

1748
02:45:51,509 --> 02:45:55,051
[SPEAKER_14]: I have stated my feelings about quid pro quos before.

1749
02:45:55,071 --> 02:46:03,617
[SPEAKER_14]: I personally do not believe in giving up things that I believe are right for our residents so that I can get some other thing I believe are right for our residents.

1750
02:46:03,637 --> 02:46:04,918
[SPEAKER_14]: So that's kind of not a thing that I do.

1751
02:46:06,559 --> 02:46:12,542
[SPEAKER_14]: But I would agree that if that is being discussed, it should be in the open and it should not be in private emails.

1752
02:46:12,562 --> 02:46:16,645
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you, Councillor Malayne.

1753
02:46:18,028 --> 02:46:20,209
[SPEAKER_12]: Yeah, I just, I want to just follow up again.

1754
02:46:20,329 --> 02:46:24,950
[SPEAKER_12]: I'm, I'm also in favor of tabling, especially when it comes to the Medford Family Network.

1755
02:46:24,970 --> 02:46:33,132
[SPEAKER_12]: I mean, we're talking about people's jobs and being able to continue a, a huge resource that I would like to see definitely outlined within the budget.

1756
02:46:33,592 --> 02:46:35,492
[SPEAKER_12]: I know so many people rely on the services.

1757
02:46:35,512 --> 02:46:38,373
[SPEAKER_12]: I know a lot of people have been waiting.

1758
02:46:38,393 --> 02:46:40,593
[SPEAKER_12]: We've been celebrating doing all these activities.

1759
02:46:41,634 --> 02:46:46,255
[SPEAKER_12]: And I, to not see it in here or to have as, as we've mentioned this email.

1760
02:46:47,975 --> 02:46:54,780
[SPEAKER_12]: I wouldn't feel comfortable moving forward with it until I actually saw it outlined in here and be able to say to residents, yes, it's in here.

1761
02:46:54,820 --> 02:46:55,501
[SPEAKER_12]: We have the funding.

1762
02:46:55,541 --> 02:46:56,701
[SPEAKER_12]: It's definitely noted.

1763
02:46:57,322 --> 02:47:02,986
[SPEAKER_12]: And people that are relying on these services, relying on the jobs, have something to look to as well.

1764
02:47:05,748 --> 02:47:06,608
[SPEAKER_20]: Thank you, Councilman Lange.

1765
02:47:06,648 --> 02:47:07,269
[SPEAKER_20]: Councilor Sang.

1766
02:47:08,289 --> 02:47:10,571
[SPEAKER_20]: I just wanted to support what you said from the chair.

1767
02:47:13,202 --> 02:47:20,228
[SPEAKER_20]: This, I think what we're being asked to give up is a very structural part of what city councils do.

1768
02:47:20,808 --> 02:47:22,970
[SPEAKER_20]: This idea that we have a branch of government.

1769
02:47:23,030 --> 02:47:31,197
[SPEAKER_20]: Again, as I said earlier tonight, we have a branch of government that's there to check and do oversight of another branch of government.

1770
02:47:31,277 --> 02:47:34,099
[SPEAKER_20]: I think it's fundamental to our form of democracy.

1771
02:47:35,220 --> 02:47:41,085
[SPEAKER_20]: And so, you know, I'm wary of giving that up.

1772
02:47:43,071 --> 02:47:51,394
[SPEAKER_20]: And like Councilor Callahan said, this idea of a quid pro quo isn't one that residents should be awfully comfortable with.

1773
02:47:52,495 --> 02:48:00,618
[SPEAKER_20]: So I think this conversation should be one to be had here in public.

1774
02:48:02,539 --> 02:48:04,119
[SPEAKER_20]: I'm thinking about the options.

1775
02:48:04,379 --> 02:48:05,620
[SPEAKER_20]: I'm trying to understand everything.

1776
02:48:06,940 --> 02:48:10,782
[SPEAKER_20]: But I think we need more information before we can make the best choice.

1777
02:48:14,477 --> 02:48:14,957
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

1778
02:48:15,358 --> 02:48:20,461
[SPEAKER_02]: I just had one slight clarifying question just so I understand too.

1779
02:48:21,221 --> 02:48:30,488
[SPEAKER_02]: Is the MFN funding and the 1.25 million for Medford Public Schools, is that also contingent on the council not cutting the budget in any way?

1780
02:48:30,508 --> 02:48:30,548
[SPEAKER_02]: Oh.

1781
02:48:34,715 --> 02:48:36,816
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you, President Beers.

1782
02:48:37,096 --> 02:48:42,857
[SPEAKER_01]: No, the $1.25 million is already in the budget for the school department as proposed.

1783
02:48:42,917 --> 02:48:47,898
[SPEAKER_01]: The MFN is just as simply as a different funding source, and that's why it's not before the council at this point in time.

1784
02:48:47,938 --> 02:48:54,400
[SPEAKER_01]: We're going to propose other free cash, essentially replenishing the capital stabilization.

1785
02:48:54,460 --> 02:49:01,202
[SPEAKER_01]: So I was going to do it together, but no issue presenting those on the 23rd and continuing the discussion on this subject.

1786
02:49:01,542 --> 02:49:02,422
[SPEAKER_02]: And just to be clear,

1787
02:49:03,677 --> 02:49:07,519
[SPEAKER_02]: those are not contingent on, the 1.25 is already in what we've received.

1788
02:49:08,079 --> 02:49:15,903
[SPEAKER_02]: And the MFN is going to be a free cash request and neither of those are contingent on us taking some sort of action, but the rest of the list is.

1789
02:49:16,223 --> 02:49:17,204
[SPEAKER_01]: That's my understanding, yes.

1790
02:49:17,604 --> 02:49:17,924
